social_posts.post_text:
My first Art Basel is officially in the books, wow, I'm incredibly grateful. 🤞🏾🥹

Much love to the @makespringhill team for bringing me in to show some pieces at the #MetaHouse 🌹

The theme of the week was "Make it, till you make it" I challenged myself to create & show pieces that represent what that means to me. In order to "make it" I believe you need a code... aka a set of values that guide you to your dreams. ✨

Each piece represents a few values that are important to me; all are named after a few of my favorite songs 🤌🏾

(L to R)
Title: Who you with II
Value: Community 

Title: LOVEHAPPY
Value: Love

Title: I'm not a star, somebody lied 
Value: Authenticity 

What's crazy is, I never really thought my art would be considered good enough to be invited into these type of spaces, but it's crazy how God will slap you in face with a reminder worthiness. 

Thank you so much to @makespringhill @meta and everyone else involved. I felt so affirmed, welcomed, and taken care of the entire time.🤞🏾

This gave me a taste of what's possible, no more playing small. See you back in Miami next year 😏

One thing about me, I'm going to take weeks, maybe months to post from trips 🫠 but I gotta circle back to Art Basel and share some of the art I experienced. 

While the events were popping it was super important for me to find time to explore different forms of art and design. Multiple people mentioned that I was going to love Design Miami and y'all know me well because, wow 🥰 I was so inspired and honestly still thinking about it. Here are a few of my faves from show. I highly recommend checking out these artists and galleries if this is your thing. 💫

And don't be surprised when I'm still posting about this in 2023. 😂🤷🏾‍♀️

1. 'Light on Water' installation by @AlbiSerfaty

2. 'Planted Air' installation by @garancevallee for @perrierjouet

3. @gaetano.pesce 'Come stai?' Chairs for @newbottega all made of resin 😍 so fire. 

4. @khaledelmays sofa x @nilufargallery I was swoon. 

5. Watched some really expensive jewelry get made at @dolcegabbana asked too many questions. 😂

6. Really still obsessed with this all felt chair by @stacklab_design 😍 had a chance to talk to the designer @forrestjeff he learned I've been seeing 111 everywhere 😂🤞🏾

7. 'Through and Through' by @tulestefactory 💙 designers: @facture_studio @ian_alistair_cochran @jt.pfeiffer @yonathanmoore.studio 

8. One of favorite color palettes for my art, stopped me in my tracks @leamestres 

9. The room of spiritual rejuvenation @studiokohler @studionadadebs

10. 'Altis Ornamentum' a shrine dedicated to the art of sport by @moniomidesign whole room was FIRE 😍
Truth be told, it's all better in real life. 🌹

A couple of weeks ago w/ @makersmark 🌹

I created art for the Makers Studio at the @la3cofficial festival. The ask was to create something inspired by women and the city of LA. This was a challenge because I could only use one color🫠 but I delivered 💁🏾‍♀️ it was super cute seeing all the guests enjoy the tote. 

@ariellev and I are big about working with clients that aren't just here for a one time exchange. We like people that are invested in who I am and want to create a long, reciprocal partnership. Shoutout to @makersmark for being a fire partner this year. 🤞🏾

As I reflect on the year, most of my projects were from clients that decided to spin the block and work with me again. That really means a lot to me and says a lot about our team 🥰 can't wait to see what happens in 2023.

Home is where the unconditional love is 🌹

1. Big L
2. Beginning 
3. Ending 
4. Fridge was running 
5. All my people with me 🤞🏾
6. Big shoes to fill 💁🏾‍♀️
7. Going into 2023
8. Queen of the city🌹
9. Territorial 4L 🤞🏾
10. Gentle reminder😏

Regardless of the outcome today, I won✨😏🏆

Created art for the NFC & AFC Super Bowl fan zone. pull up on me at the stadium. 🤞🏾🌹 

Happy Super Bowl 💁🏾‍♀️

Yesterday was absolutely beautiful 🥹 I was honored for Black History Month by @fortuneandforks and celebrated with some of my closest friends & community. 🌹🤞🏾

I'm still soaking it all in. Receiving my flowers in real time really means the world to me. I don't think I could ever express my gratitude without losing all my lashes. ✨

@naomiwrighttt & @krystalvega thank you for founding this community. It's always a good time and a safe space. I really appreciate y'all for seeing and embracing me. 🌹

Yesterday reminded me that showing up as my authentic self is always good enough and never goes unnoticed. Thank you so much to everyone that pulled up. The love is real 🥹🤞🏾

Major shoutout to @bayabgin for helping us celebrate 🌹 I think it's safe to say you have a new fan in all of us. A time was had. ✨

So icy entertainment 🏂 w/ @hikeclerb 

Last weekend was full of a lot of firsts. My first time visiting mammoth, first time snowboarding, and first time experiencing a real blizzard. Going into a lot of unknowns really brought out my inner child in a way that was unexpected and much needed. 

"Exploration" is a big theme on my vision board for the year. I want to try new things, go different places, and explore life outside of my comfort zone. I want to push myself to actually LIVE and the trip did just that. 

This experience also reminded me of all the spaces we (Black ppl) aren't naturally included in or apart of. It placed a fire under my ass to go harder and never stop taking up space. 🤞🏾 I encourage y'all to do the same. 

Also, I'm so proud of @evemeetswest for building this community and providing WOC with all types of experiences in nature. This is only the beginning ❄️🤟🏾 love you!
Don't worry, it's not too late to add me to your vision boards. 🌹 📸: @exquisite_eye

So @thatsmyyjam said she wanted to jump out of a plane for her 30th birthday. So what did we do? We Jumped 14,000 feet out of an airplane 🙌🏾 easily one of the best things I've experienced. The level of peace and stillness up there is unmatched and very unexpected. 

I'm ready to do it again. Definitely telling the kids I was Amelia Earhart 😂 Real fly girl shit. 🪂
I'm not sure what to say here. I'm sure you see what's going on. 🌹 📸: @orixa.jpg

Last year, I started buying flowers for myself everyyyy Friday. That quickly became the thing I would look forward to every week. An easy way to show myself love and bring a lil razzle dazzle to my space. 💐✨

This year, I committed myself to exploring all my interests and develop hobbies that aren't rooted in monetary gain but only creative expression. So in between my visits to my local florist (shoutout to @romelsflowers) I started making my own arrangements and I'm in love with the process. It's so freeing and beautiful. 

Ive been obsessed with figuring out how my perspective translates into different forms of artistry. My love for color and texture moves into everything I do. 🤞🏾

Buy yourself flowers, you deserve them. 🌹

Before the Super Bowl, there was the Grammys 😏💁🏾‍♀️ I had the opportunity to create the visual identity for the Universal Music Group artist showcase + Grammy after party. ✨

One of my favorite things about being a multidisciplinary artist is the ability to exist in multiple spaces with multiple skill sets. I love to see art and design adapted to different formats and spaces. Always a reminder to myself that there is no ceiling. I exist everywhere. 🤌🏾

Back in 2021, @jumpman23 took us out to Utah for our first trip as the LA Women's Jordan Brand Collective. 🌹

Fast forward to today, and the Jordan 1 Elevate "Salt Lake City" has released. An exclusive women's shoe designed and inspired by our trip to Utah. 

I'm super excited to be apart of this campaign with my people. And always grateful to be apart of the Jordan Brand family. 🥹

I've said this before, but I've loved sneakers, in particularly Jordan's my entire life. it's still so wild to work and be seen in this space. Let's see what happens next. ✨

📸: @mayaiman🌹
makeup: @vanessakeri 🤌🏾
Bob 💁🏾‍♀️: @nikkiallyrae ✨
Supa Laci with my Supa friends 🌹🦸🏾‍♀️

📍The Goldwyn House @thefutureperfect 

Lately I've been following my love for beautiful places, spaces, and objects. Trying to understand with greater intention why I like the things I like, and how these things add to my overall perspective & artistry. I'm definitely in a season of exploration and spontaneity. 🌹

The space is absolutely beautiful and very intentional, even down to the smell of it. 🤌🏾 I originally came to see exhibition from @gaetano.pesce (after seeing his work during Basel I became obsessed) but TBH the whole thing blew me away. @colinking KILLED the styling. I want to live there 😩

A bunch of my close friends (shoutout to y'all) mentioned I should start sharing the things that inspire me and my lil nerdy adventures so I'm finally trying it out... enjoy lol!

April was challenging, but very good for me 🥰🌹 The people claim that your birthdate/birthday month is the real start of the new year and it definitely feels like it. Lots of new beginnings, self reflection, and fresh perspectives. I'm excited for what's next. ✨

Ps: thanks for all the birthday love, I swear I'm going to catch up on my messages one day. 💁🏾‍♀️
Couldn't wait, we starting summer now. 🌹✨

Everyday I take a walk or drive around the neighborhood and everyday I see something different and beautiful that I didn't see the day before.

Today's views 🌹

New mural art for the debut of @culturecon Los Angeles ✨💁🏾‍♀️

If you know me, you know I've been more intentional and ducked off this year....CultureCon was my first realll "outside" LA event of the year, so I had a lot of social anxiety leading up to it. 

Come to find out, it was exactlyyy what I needed 🥹 the amount of love that was poured into me and my artistry through community was unmatched. Watching y'all get flicks off, and have so much joy, really filled my spirit. 🥰

Opportunities like this are always my favorite, because not only do I get to create for my people, but I get to see the reaction and appreciation in real time. 🤞🏾 

Thank y'all so much for the love and support and a HUGE thank you to the @theccnyc team for always uplifting and including me. Means the world to be seen by my people. 🥰

📸: @mayaiman @jamdownflava @chuckmarcus 

Ps: y'all really reminded me that I'm THAT girl last weekend lmao! I hit one of my group chats like "y'all I guess it's not all hype, I'm REALLY her. Thats crazy" 😂

“Can you see me?” A collection of 20 interior art pieces for the new @warbyparker Bishop Ranch location in San Ramon, CA. 💁🏾‍♀️

This collection of art was heavily inspired by the community and landscape of the city, while also including elements from the Warby Parker brand. ✨

My hope is that anyone can walk into this store and feel represented/seen. Thank you so much to the @warbyparker team for commissioning me for this. 

We in a store y’all. 20/20 vision. Super clear. 😏

Creative direction & design for @colorcreative Find Your People Program launch party 🥰💁🏾‍♀️ 

FYPP provides training, resources, mentorship, and guidance for up-and-coming and underrepresented creatives. Keeping that in mind, I wanted to creative a visual identity rooted in connectivity, empowerment, and really just some fly, fun shit. 😏

If you know me, you know I have a moodboard for EVERYTHING and I love making them... I included my moodboard for this so you can see how the direction translated into the event. 🥰🤞🏾

Ps: Much love to my people that always recommend me for opportunities and speak highly of me in rooms I'm not in. People always ask me how I get these jobs, or assume I'm represented by an art agency. Whole time it's been God & community, and I'm very thankful for that. 🤞🏾

Thank you! @colorcreative @kaysiaaa & @talithawatkins love y'all! ✨
Floral design: @toboreoweh 🌹

Last year I discovered @danielle_mckinney_ art and I've been obsessed every since. It's rare that I find an artist where EVERY single piece they create I love and feel seen in. 🥹

I'm not sure if it's the red nail accents or the fact she's from Alabama.... but it's something about her art that I'm so fascinated and connected with. It's too good to stay in my camera roll. 

Owning a piece of hers is on my vision board. 🔮 check her out.

For the next 30 days I'm challenging myself to create something new or do something inspiring/creative everyday. I completed day 1 yesterday with an Incense making class 🥰

One thing I've been adamant about this year is living a more intentional creative life, and not just when I'm creating things for clients. I've been inspired to take it up a notch and really find ways to stimulate my creativity every single day.... it can be as simple as trying a new drink recipe or visiting a new library. I'm in a space where all I want to do is create and learn. I'm hungry & eager. 

I know by me putting it out into the world it adds another layer of accountability and gives me less room to BS lol 🫠 I may or may not post each day in real time, because life... but I'll share when I can. 

Friends, please hold me accountable and don't be surprised when I ask y'all to join me on an adventure. 💁🏾‍♀️

Now... let me go figure out day 2 🫠

Day 2 & 3 of creating something new, or doing something new that's creative or inspiring everyday ✨

Day 2: if you know me, or pay attention to the things I post, you know I LOVE to make a cocktail. One of my good friends got me a mixology book and it's so fascinating/extensive. To me, the culinary field is its own world of artistry. There's a technique to everything, from how you layer a drink to the type of ice you need for a certain consistency. 

I've been so obsessed with learning more so I decided to try a cocktail I've never made with a spirit I don't use as often. The book also goes into depth about the origin of each spirit, giving you knowledge on how to properly use it. Another part of making drinks that I LOVE is making them for my friends. I love watching them take the first sip, and just feeling good 🥰 it's very comforting. 

Day 3: I've been very interested in learning more about how things are built. I want to understand materials, fabrication, and objects on a different scale, as I plan to take my artistry in that direction. A homie put me on @amsterdammodern so I decided to pull up for some research. It felt like "right place, right time" because I was able to chop it with one of the employees and learn A LOT about what I want to do. 

In conclusion, my ideas for product aren't far fetched... and now I know more knowledge on how to do it. Crazy how this challenge is already putting me in the right places.

More soon. Sorry for the long caption 🤷🏾‍♀️

I'm still on my 30 day challenge of creating something new or doing something creative/inspiring each day. I have no idea what day I'm on 😂 but here's a few things I've been doing. ✨

Art exhibits, car shows, library days, creating with friends and their kids (Isla is basically Picasso 🥰), coloring, creating color palettes for future use, beach days, revisiting art history (shoutout to @_ajgirard for inviting me to tour Luna Luna), and lotsss of painting. 🥰

One of my favorite parts of this challenge, is that I've had a bunch of friends hit me to join me on some of my adventures or they've put me on different things to see and try. A reminder than I'm never in my journey alone🤞🏾

I'm feeling more inspired and creative than I've been all year. Love that for me. 🌹 more soon.

Archives & Studio Vault Sale ✨

If I had to give one word to describe this year so far, I would say TRANSFORMATION. 🤌🏾 There’s been so many realizations, both about myself and my artistry. I’m currently in a season of purging; making space for new ideas, new art, new mediums, and new perspectives. In order to make space for the new, I’m getting rid of the old. 

With that being said, I have a few prints and pins from the studio for sale. Please note this will be the last time these items are available. Once they’re gone, they’re GONE. No restocks. I gave the folks that have been on my email list for years first dibs yesterday, so act quick 🥰

I've had a lot of fun going down memory lane; looking at old artwork, products, and journals that I've created over the years. It's so crazy how much your past can inform and inspire your future. I'm excited to explore a new era of self. More soon ✨

Ps: this will also be the last time you see my website in its current form 😏 I’ve been working on some upgrades that I can’t wait to share. It's time to take things to the next level. 🤞🏾

Shop link in bio 🌹

@beyonce really showed out on her birthday and I'm still not over it 😩 She had me feeling like I could build a house from scratch with my bare acrylics when it was over. 

Mentally, I'm still at Sofi 🐝 but about to run it back in Texas 🤟🏾

Awhile ago I was having a conversation with my therapist about how my friends are like my family... by the end of the convo she made realize my friends aren't like my family, they ARE my family 🥹

Last weekend was filled with so much love and family. I was able to see one of my best friends of 15+ years marry her person 🥺 which is CRAZY because I feel like we were JUST in college. I was also surrounded by most of my best friends all weekend. The whole time I kept yelling "I get to turn my brain off this weekend" which is true.... I don't think or worry about much when I'm with them... just love and a good time.

It doesn't matter how much time goes by, how far we live from each other, we always show up... and I'm forever grateful. 

Anyway, I hope y'all fools know.... y'all heal me a lil bit every time I see y'all 🥰🤞🏾till death do us part 😂💍
PT. 2: Houston owes me nothing but a Ricola, Goody powder, and a bottle of water. ❤️‍🔥

One of my favorite parts about being an artist is ability show up and exist in spaces that my physical body has never stepped foot in. The gift to have my presence/spirit felt through visual communication with little to no words. You don't need to physically see me, but my representation is always there, never too far away. 🔮

Was I at Afrotech? No. But my art was, so technically, yes! 🥰 I enjoyed seeing the beautiful Black faces interacting with my art. Thank you @meta ✨

I'm not sure when I woke up and became Suzy Homemaker 😩 but these days I find an exceptionallll amount of joy in hosting friends, decorating, making flower arrangements, crafting bomb cocktails, becoming a better cook, screaming into Karaoke mics in my living room, and really just creating cozy ass environments for my friends and I. 

All that to say, I hosted an intimate Friendsgiving w/ the homies for the first time and the vibes were super cute 🥰 all year I've been hollering "I wanna host more things at the crib" and I'm finally feeling more inspired to do it. ✨

Ps: I was so obsessed with taking pics of my table, that the only food pic I took was the in progress macaroni and cheese that I needed to send my mama for accuracy 😭 but everybody brought dishes and I didn't make it past the first plate 😩 10/10

If you happen to watch the new Melo & Mero podcast and notice a big colorful piece of art dedicated to New York in the back just know it's me 🥰

I was tapped to create a NY inspired map (w/ emphasis on Brooklyn) for the set of their new show @7pminbrooklyn ✨

Many thanks to @jocelynn_williams for thinking of me for this project (and you killed the set design) My brothers and nephews think I'm super cool now 😂🤞🏾❤️‍🔥

#WBPartner – When Warner Bros hit me and asked to partner on art for the release of @TheColorPurple, the scene I wanted to reference popped into my mind immediately! If you’ve seen the original film you already know this reference, and in my opinion it’s one of the most iconic and memorable. 💜

While The Color Purple touches on a lot of themes, I really wanted to create something that feels like joy, sisterhood, and playfulness; all elements I love to include in images I create.✨

I always say my artwork is a reflection of everyday life, a mirror of how I view the world. Film is such a strong way to cement images in culture that can be referenced for a lifetime. 

Grab your mama, sister, friends, auntie, and em, and check out #TheColorPurpleMovie on Christmas Day. 

Animation: Imaginary Lava 
@WBPictures #PurpleLove

A conversation at a museum a few weeks ago that went from "damn, we should've made a product for the holidays, we'll do it next year" to...actually, let's not overthink it and just do it now; let's make something Black AF for our friends and family for Christmas. 

The result: A Black ass Santa wrapping paper. Designed, executed, and produced in like 7 days 😭 the first of many Laci x @homme.ware product collabs 🤌🏾

Shoutout to @ashkidash + @unwrp for producing this for us so quickly. Love you! 

In 2024, there's no more waiting around, we getting stuff done now. 🤞🏾

I'm going to tell my kids that back in my day....legend says if you were good, Santa would pull up with presents in a Porsche. 

And if you were reallyyyyy good, those presents were wrapped in Black Santa magical wrapping paper designed by somebody special. 👀😂

Honestly, I think y'all should start telling that story now. 😭 Merry Christmas from Laci Claus 🎄

Last year I said I wanted more hobbies in 2023, and making flower arrangements for myself has become my favorite past time. This one was for my Christmas decor, and the biggest one I've made so far.🌹

I love figuring out how to incorporate my love for color and texture into different mediums.

And I also just love having beautiful, fly, fresh flowers  in the crib at all times. 🤌🏾🌹

“If we’re lucky, we get to die several times in our lifetime. Not a physical death, but one where we shed the person we once were for us to become who we are in the present, changing the trajectory of our future. Realigning ourselves mentally and spiritually, tapping into our higher being. Going through periods of unlearning and removing the boxes society places us in” – @iamgmjohnson 
 
Death and rebirth are common themes in my life, in the sense of that I'm always learning, growing, and outgrowing different parts of myself. It's often stressful, because I'm stubborn 🫡 but this year I've learned to lean into it. 

Every time I feel like I'm transitioning into a new version of myself, I document it with photos, and I always go to @jassieuo 🥰

Usually, we create a colorful curated moodboard, and a fit and makeup planned. This time felt very different though, I wanted something simple and soft... no bells and whistles; just face.

In Jasmine's words "let's just focus on your essence and energy, let's focus on how you're feeling" the answer to that is this portrait... I feel the most like myself than I've ever felt... strong but soft, sensual, aware, and ready. ❤️‍🔥

This is a snippet of my vision/mood board from 2023.

A couple of months ago, I showed this to @kristena_deyon and I was complaining about the fact that I felt like I didn't achieve anythinggg on my vision board this for year. 

Kristena quickly pointed out that I actually achieved a lot... but it wasn't the professional achievements, it was the physical, mental, and spiritual ones. 🥹

My mom often says "I love how you take care of yourself" and by that she doesn't mean cosmetically... she means the effort I put into my life that most people don't see....like therapy, diving deep into figuring myself out, strengthening my relationship w/ God, taking care of my body, creating healthy boundaries, figuring out how to be a better friend/daughter/sister, listening more and talking less, acknowledging and working on insecurities, spending time in nature, becoming more vulnerable... etc. 

Those things are my major accomplishments for this year. Similar to a lot of posts I've been seeing, 2023 was the ghetto 🫠 but I feel like the lessons I've learned, and the amount of time I've spent deeply working on myself has set me up for an amazing 2024 ❤️‍🔥

Since this is the time of year where we posts our wins, I think it's the perfect time to remind folks that you are good enough even if you feel like you didn't achieve something. 

Happy New Year 🤞🏾✨🥰

Black & white, so you don't miss the fine print. ✨
📸: @jassieuo

The people are not lying when they say home is where the heart is 🥹 the amount of love that I both felt and shared with my family and friends this holiday season really set the tone for my year. It reminded me that I'm never without love, and that I'm loved unconditionally.

My mommy really showed out this trip though....Given, she always spoils me when I'm home 💁🏾‍♀️ but this time was different. She's one of few people that really know how rough 2023 was for me, and how much I deserved a little ease and celebration in my life. 

She threw me a surprised dinner with family, friends, and community leaders that helped raised me..... we talking teachers, track coaches, girls inc leaders etc. People who knew me before I knew me 🥹 I've always wanted a surprise dinner/party and that was so incredibly special to me. The love that was poured into me was abundant.

Aside from dinner I just felt a sense of ease/love overall.... home cooked meals, plated breakfast in bed, vulnerable conversations, intentional quality time, and lots & lots of laughter. Everything I needed and more 🫶🏾

This post is really just dedicated to my mama because I love her downnn. She doesn't know it, but the things I learned from her while at home are going to change the trajectory of my life. I needed that time so bad. Love you. ❤️‍🔥

Ps: I may or may not have cried all the way to the airport 😩
